{"id":1268056073,"question_id":3444,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"2 weeks, 3 days","timestamp":1716692513,"status":11,"status_display":"Wrong Answer","runtime":"N/A","url":"/submissions/detail/1268056073/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Find the Number of Good Pairs II","memory":"N/A","code":"class Solution {\n    public long numberOfPairs(int[] nums1, int[] nums2, int k) {\n        \n        int m = nums1.length;\n        int n = nums2.length;\n        int cnt = 0;\n        \n        Map<Integer, Integer> map1 = new HashMap<>();\n        Map<Integer, Integer> map2 = new HashMap<>();\n        \n        for(int i=0; i<m; i++){\n            \n            \n            \n            if(nums1[i]%k!=0) continue;\n            \n            \n            map1.put(nums1[i], map1.getOrDefault(nums1[i],0)+1);\n            \n        }\n        \n        \n        \n        for(int j=0; j<n; j++){\n            map2.put(nums2[j], map2.getOrDefault(nums2[j],0)+1);            \n        }\n        \n        for(int k1 : map1.keySet()){\n            for(int k2 : map2.keySet()){\n                if(k1%k2==0   ){\n                    cnt+= map1.get(k1)*map2.get(k2);\n                }\n            }\n        }\n        \n        return cnt;\n        \n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"find-the-number-of-good-pairs-ii","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
